                guarantee they will be available at all times. Services may be
                temporarily unavailable due to maintenance, updates, or
                circumstances beyond our control.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section id="registration">
              <h2>4. Registration and Account</h2>

              <h3>4.1 Eligibility</h3>
              <p>To use our Services, you must:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Be 18 years or older, or have parental/guardian consent</li>
                <li>
                  Be an alumnus, current student, or related to the data science
                  field
                </li>
                <li>Provide accurate and up-to-date information</li>
                <li>Maintain the confidentiality of your access credentials</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>4.2 Registration</h3>
              <p>
                To access certain features, you must create an account by
                providing:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Basic personal information (name, email, etc.)</li>
                <li>Academic and professional information</li>
                <li>A secure password</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>4.3 Account Responsibility</h3>
              <p>You are responsible for:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Maintaining the security of your account and password</li>
                <li>All activities that occur under your account</li>
                <li>Immediately notifying us about any unauthorized use</li>
                <li>Keeping your contact information updated</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="acceptable-use">
              <h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>

              <h3>5.1 Permitted Conduct</h3>
              <p>You may use our Services for:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Legitimate professional networking</li>
                <li>Searching or posting real job opportunities</li>
                <li>Participating in community events and activities</li>
                <li>Sharing professional knowledge and experiences</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>5.2 Prohibited Conduct</h3>
              <p>You may NOT use our Services to:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Post false, misleading, or fraudulent content</li>
                <li>Harass, intimidate, or discriminate against other users</li>
                <li>Send spam or unsolicited communications</li>
                <li>Violate other users' privacy</li>
                <li>Attempt to access accounts that don't belong to you</li>
                <li>Interfere with the operation of the Services</li>
                <li>Use the Services for illegal activities</li>
                <li>Collect user information without consent</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>5.3 Consequences</h3>
              <p>Violation of these rules may result in:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Warnings</li>
                <li>Temporary account suspension</li>
                <li>Permanent account termination</li>
                <li>Legal action when appropriate</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="user-content">
              <h2>6. User Content</h2>

              <h3>6.1 Your Content</h3>
