                to use our Services for your personal and non-commercial use,
                subject to these Terms.
              </p>

              <h3>7.3 Restrictions</h3>
              <p>You may not:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Copy, modify, or distribute our content without permission
                </li>
                <li>Use our trademarks without authorization</li>
                <li>Reverse engineer our Services</li>
                <li>Create derivative works based on our Services</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>7.4 DMCA</h3>
              <p>
                We respect intellectual property rights. If you believe your
                work has been copied in a way that constitutes copyright
                infringement, contact us with details of the alleged
                infringement.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section id="privacy">
              <h2>8. Privacy</h2>

              <p>
                Your privacy is important to us. Our handling of your personal
                information is governed by our <a href="/en/privacy"
                  >Privacy Policy</a
                >, which is incorporated by reference into these Terms.
              </p>

              <p>
                By using our Services, you agree to the collection and use of
                information in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section id="termination">
              <h2>9. Termination</h2>

              <h3>9.1 Termination by User</h3>
              <p>
                You may terminate your account at any time by deactivating it
                through your account settings or by contacting us directly.
              </p>

              <h3>9.2 Termination by SECiD</h3>
              <p>We may suspend or terminate your account immediately if:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>You violate these Terms</li>
                <li>
                  Your use of the Services causes harm to other users or SECiD
                </li>
                <li>Required for legal compliance</li>
                <li>We decide to discontinue the Services</li>
              </ul>

              <h3>9.3 Effects of Termination</h3>
              <p>Upon termination:</p>
              <ul>
                <li>Your right to use the Services ends immediately</li>
                <li>
                  We may delete or retain your information according to our
                  Privacy Policy
                </li>
                <li>
                  Provisions that by their nature should survive will continue
                  in effect
                </li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="limitation-liability">
              <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>

              <h3>10.1 Disclaimer of Warranties</h3>
              <p>
                The Services are provided "as is" and "as available". We offer
                no express or implied warranties about the Services.
              </p>

              <h3>10.2 Limitation of Damages</h3>
              <p>
                In no event shall SECiD be liable for indirect, incidental,
                special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of
                profits, data, or use, incurred by you or third parties.
              </p>

              <h3>10.3 Total Liability Limit</h3>
              <p>
                Our total liability to you for any claim related to these Terms
                or the Services shall not exceed the amount paid by you to SECiD
                in the 12 months preceding the event giving rise to the claim.
              </p>

              <h3>10.4 Indemnification</h3>
              <p>
                You agree to indemnify and hold harmless SECiD from any claim,
                damage, loss, or expense (including attorney fees) arising from
                your use of the Services or violation of these Terms.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section id="governing-law">
              <h2>11. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>

              <h3>11.1 Governing Law</h3>
              <p>
                These Terms are governed by the laws of Mexico, without regard
